<subSubSection id="114E0530356E5DCE15C942E7AE2633E5" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A32907A19221960C3C56618C24B853BB" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="908140D077E07AC714D2295B8689B067" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
Native to the Palaearctic region, trans-Palaearctic (
<bibRefCitation id="C234FFFCEBB47E05E4091BB1913A95E0" author="Schuelke, M" editor="Assing, V" journalOrPublisher="PhD Thesis, Michigan State University, Department of Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" refId="B185" refString="Schuelke, M, Assing, V, Schuelke, M, 2012a. Oxytelinae. In: AssingVSchuelkeM (Eds) Die Kaefer Mitteleuropas, Band 4 (2.Auflage). Spektrum Akademischer Verlag, Heidelberg, 283-284." title="Oxytelinae. In: AssingVSchuelkeM (Eds) Die Kaefer Mitteleuropas, Band 4 (2. Auflage). Spektrum Akademischer Verlag, Heidelberg, 283 - 284." year="2012 a">
<normalizedToken id="599D2F60D18F0C5005246E7D74BDD497" originalValue="Schülke">Schuelke</normalizedToken>
2012a
</bibRefCitation>
). Adventive in the Nearctic region (Maryland, Massachusetts, New Jersey, New York, and Pennsylvania, United States, and Ontario, Quebec, New Brunswick, and Newfoundland, Canada (
<bibRefCitation id="892C237CFA9C18044C83B42B00E90DB5" author="Herman, L" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="111 - 254" refId="B90" refString="Herman, L, 1972. Revision of Bledius and related genera. Part I. The aequatorialis, mandibularis, and semiferrugineus groups and two new genera (Coleopera, Staphylinidae, Oxytelinae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 149: 111 - 254" title="Revision of Bledius and related genera. Part I. The aequatorialis, mandibularis, and semiferrugineus groups and two new genera (Coleopera, Staphylinidae, Oxytelinae)." volume="149" year="1972">Herman 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2AB28422ABAE9658E816F61CC3DD2FA9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.360.4742" author="Bousquet, Y" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="1 - 44" refId="B27" refString="Bousquet, Y, Bouchard, P, Davies, A, Sikes, D, 2013. Checklist of beetles (Coleoptera) of Canada and Alaska. Second edition. ZooKeys 360: 1 - 44" title="Checklist of beetles (Coleoptera) of Canada and Alaska. Second edition." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.360.4742" volume="360" year="2013">Bousquet et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="B59E684A5FD2667F659FF5EDE4902A4D" genus="B." lsidName="B. philadelphicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="philadelphicus">
<emphasis id="EADC42D42F10916739B79520AFB15D7D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">B. philadelphicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B8A138CA6BEF1F343C5DAA507B9D3796" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="canadian records">
<paragraph id="B97D5BEDC67FD902A2FF0DB988369A1F" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Canadian records</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5EC657E9EF3F801DBB8B67AE41B383A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">(DNA barcoded specimens). Ontario: Georgian Bay Islands National Park, 19-Aug-2013 to 27-Aug-2013 (1 ex, CBG); Grundy Lake Provincial Park, 13-Jul-1995 (1 ex, CNC); Hamilton, 21-Jul-2017 (3 exx, CBG). Quebec: Montreal, 19-Aug-1981 (1 ex, CNC).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4C54EE2896BF2FA10B3EBD04215408FF" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="additional canadian records">
<paragraph id="BD74499923D00CED49F52D282F44B085" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Additional Canadian records.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA1EBB899BCEA5C26EA1F90E34B721AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
See 
<bibRefCitation id="CB63E158DA5E3C8E2141E32D885730FD" author="Herman, L" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="111 - 254" refId="B90" refString="Herman, L, 1972. Revision of Bledius and related genera. Part I. The aequatorialis, mandibularis, and semiferrugineus groups and two new genera (Coleopera, Staphylinidae, Oxytelinae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 149: 111 - 254" title="Revision of Bledius and related genera. Part I. The aequatorialis, mandibularis, and semiferrugineus groups and two new genera (Coleopera, Staphylinidae, Oxytelinae)." volume="149" year="1972">Herman (1972)</bibRefCitation>
for a list of earlier records from Canada and the United States (as 
<taxonomicName id="571AAABE7FD67E6045DE2FEA1FB6DCB5" genus="B." lsidName="B. philadelphicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="philadelphicus">
<emphasis id="ABF745835F3E07A5E4ED70275A38973A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">B. philadelphicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B08088AF2DC6292EA307922E32DCAA46" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="diagnostic information">
<paragraph id="C8FD5F3A95F697AC12C18EECB1C40A8B" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Diagnostic information.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B55098CA8200CEBA05865C416D72E63" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
